chunks.html_content: You could be imprisoned, banned from driving and face a fine if you’re found guilty of drink-driving.
chunks.plain_content:
Drink-driving penalties
You could be imprisoned, banned from driving and face a fine if you’re found guilty of drink-driving.

heading_context: Being in charge of a vehicle while above the legal limit or unfit through drink
chunks.html_content:
The actual penalty you get is up to the magistrates who hear your case, and depends on your offence.

You may be able to reduce your ban by taking a drink-drive rehabilitation scheme (DDRS) course if you’re banned from driving for 12 months or more. It’s up to the court to offer this.

You may get:

  • 3 months’ imprisonment
  • up to £2,500 fine
  • a possible driving ban
chunks.plain_content:
Drink-driving penalties
Being in charge of a vehicle while above the legal limit or unfit through drink
The actual penalty you get is up to the magistrates who hear your case, and depends on your offence.
You may be able to reduce your ban by taking a drink-drive rehabilitation scheme (DDRS) course if you’re banned from driving for 12 months or more. It’s up to the court to offer this.
You may get:

  3 months’ imprisonment
  up to £2,500 fine
  a possible driving ban

heading_context: Driving or attempting to drive while above the legal limit or unfit through drink
chunks.html_content:
You may get:

  • 6 months’ imprisonment
  • an unlimited fine
  • a driving ban for at least 1 year (3 years if convicted twice in 10 years)
chunks.plain_content:
Drink-driving penalties
Driving or attempting to drive while above the legal limit or unfit through drink
You may get:

  6 months’ imprisonment
  an unlimited fine
  a driving ban for at least 1 year (3 years if convicted twice in 10 years)

heading_context: Refusing to provide a specimen of breath, blood or urine for analysis
chunks.html_content:
You may get:

  • 6 months’ imprisonment
  • an unlimited fine
  • a ban from driving for at least 1 year
chunks.plain_content:
Drink-driving penalties
Refusing to provide a specimen of breath, blood or urine for analysis
You may get:

  6 months’ imprisonment
  an unlimited fine
  a ban from driving for at least 1 year

heading_context: Causing death by careless driving when under the influence of drink
chunks.html_content:
You may get:

  • life imprisonment
  • an unlimited fine
  • a ban from driving for at least 5 years
  • an extended driving test before your licence is returned
chunks.plain_content:
Drink-driving penalties
Causing death by careless driving when under the influence of drink
You may get:

  life imprisonment
  an unlimited fine
  a ban from driving for at least 5 years
  an extended driving test before your licence is returned

heading_context: Causing death by careless driving when under the influence of drink
chunks.html_content: You will not automatically get your licence back if you’re a high risk offender.
chunks.plain_content:
Drink-driving penalties
Causing death by careless driving when under the influence of drink
You will not automatically get your licence back if you’re a high risk offender.

chunks.html_content:
A conviction for drink-driving also means:

  • your car insurance costs will increase significantly
  • if you drive for work, your employer will see your conviction on your licence
  • you may have trouble travelling to countries like the USA
chunks.plain_content:
Drink-driving penalties
Other problems you could face
A conviction for drink-driving also means:

  your car insurance costs will increase significantly
  if you drive for work, your employer will see your conviction on your licence
  you may have trouble travelling to countries like the USA
